      <title>Reading Notes：Feature Shrinkage Pyramid for Camouflaged Object Detection with Transformers</title>
      <link href="/2023/06/08/blog1/"/>
      <url>/2023/06/08/blog1/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Feature-Shrinkage-Pyramid-for-Camouflaged-Object-Detection-with-Transformers"><a href="#Feature-Shrinkage-Pyramid-for-Camouflaged-Object-Detection-with-Transformers" class="headerlink" title="Feature Shrinkage Pyramid for Camouflaged Object Detection with Transformers"></a>Feature Shrinkage Pyramid for Camouflaged Object Detection with Transformers</h1><h2 id="Motivation"><a href="#Motivation" class="headerlink" title="Motivation"></a>Motivation</h2><p>They found that Vision Transformers have two limitations in Camouflaged Object Detection. </p><ol><li>Less effective locality modeling</li><li>Insufficient feature aggregation in decoders</li></ol><p>This is not conducive to camouflaged object detection models from searching for subtle clues in indistinguishable backgrounds.</p><h2 id="Two-Blocks"><a href="#Two-Blocks" class="headerlink" title="Two Blocks"></a>Two Blocks</h2><ul><li>AIM (Adjacent Interaction Modules)</li><li>FSD (Features Shrinkage Decoder)</li></ul><p><img src="/Blog1/fig1.png" alt="fig1"></p>]]></content>
      
      
